The paper deals with dimensionality reduction, which is a topic in both computer science and mathematics. The use of linear maps and the $\ell_2$ norm suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). The focus on distortion and the use of lower bounds suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of geometric arguments and the mention of the Johnson-Lindenstrauss lemma suggest that the paper may belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CC) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
